Putting points into your shield skill also gives you a better chance to block attacks (melee, magical bolts and arrows) along with giving you special moves.<br>
<br>
Putting points into parry only increases your chances of parrying, it'll be easier to use combat styles based off of parry.<br>
<br>
When attacked, the game checks evade first, then block(if you have a shield) and then parry(if you have the skill).<br>
<br>
Here's the formula for figuring out your chances of avoiding attacks:<br>
<br>
Chance of Blocking: 5%+(0.5%*shield skill)<br>
Chance of Parrying: 5%+(0.5%*parry skill)<br>
<br>
Not sure about Evade 1,2,3,4 but I think that it's 5%, 10%, 15%, and 20% chance to avoid attacks.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps some. Plus there's an Advice channel where you can ask questions and stuff to other people in game that will be able to help you out as well.<br>
